Package net.minestom.server.instance

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BlockModifier
    Represents an element which can place blocks at position.
    ChunkGenerator
    Responsible for the Chunk generation, can be set using Instance.setChunkGenerator(ChunkGenerator).
    ChunkPopulator  
    ExplosionSupplier  
    IChunkLoader
    Interface implemented to change the way chunks are loaded/saved.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Chunk
    A chunk is a part of an Instance, limited by a size of 16x256x16 blocks and subdivided in 16 sections of 16 blocks height.
    DynamicChunk
    Represents a Chunk which store each individual block in memory.
    Explosion
    Abstract explosion.
    Instance
    Instances are what are called "worlds" in Minecraft, you can add an entity in it using Entity.setInstance(Instance).
    InstanceContainer
    InstanceContainer is an instance that contains chunks in contrary to SharedInstance.
    InstanceManager
    Used to register Instance.
    MinestomBasicChunkLoader
    A IChunkLoader used by InstanceContainer which is based on the StorageLocation and ChunkSupplier associated to it.
    SharedInstance
    The SharedInstance is an instance that shares the same chunks as its linked InstanceContainer, entities are separated.
    WorldBorder
    Represents the world border of an Instance, can be retrieved with Instance.getWorldBorder().
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    WorldBorder.CollisionAxis
